      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, if you're feeling great and your tests are normal, a lower dose of warfarin can be considered. However, it's crucial to monitor your INR levels closely and consult with your healthcare provider before making any changes. Warfarin is a delicate balance, and even if you're feeling fine, your body might still be on the edge. Keep an eye on any signs of bleeding or bruising, and don't hesitate to reach out for professional advice.",
