      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's true that a stable INR indicates your body has adapted, but warfarin's effects can be unpredictable. Reducing to 2mg without a gradual tapering plan and close monitoring could indeed be dangerous. Your body might not maintain the same stability at a lower dose, leading to potential complications. I strongly advise against self-adjusting your dosage. Let's find a safe and effective way to manage your medication together. Your health is too important to take chances with.",
      "source": "target",
